Sentencas: In this research, an inverse approach is presented to determine multi-physicochemical properties of electrodes using cell polarization performance measurements and repulsive particle swarm optimization technique, without resorting to porous microstructure features, e.g., porosity, tortuosity, pore size.
Titulo: Inverse approach to quantify multi-physicochemical properties of porous electrodes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The mathematical model is developed using a proton conducting button cell test stand as the physical base and employed for inverse analysis.

Sentencas: The approach is demonstrated using both simulated results and practical measurements.
